items.name: Hayden's YiffMix
items.description:
Hello reader!

This model mix was found by 'accident' a month or two ago and has decent requests on Furry Diffusion for it to be available for download so here it is. It can do both safe and mature works.

The mix is supposed to handle traditional art and classic 'toony' furry styles, but as the base models used for mixes are seemingly moving away from that it is a good idea to try all versions if you cannot get something specific to work right.

As such: 1.2 is a good starting point. 1.4 could/will result in different poses and scenes.

But with that said, the fault is obvious and I am working almost every day for more, better tuning, finding the faults or strength of the model.

For instance:

  • Extremely high background detail, even without LoRa's. Especially when using hires fix can get very fancy things built into the background of whatever scene you, the director is trying to create.

  • Newer models might have issues with eyes, as the artist data gets a bit 'messy'. Thus, it is recommended to explicitly mention what color eyes you want, and pupils if applicable. Adding or removing artist tags can also help a ton in this case.

  • Extremely niche Kinks/fetish works might need older model versions like 1.2, this is a known thing so I'm working on it.

Otherwise, new models are at the mercy of others since this is a tuned mix of other tuned mixes for maximum detail and universability, or that is the idea.

Don't forget to join the Furry Diffusion Discord for discussions and postings of everyone's work: --> https://discord.gg/furrydiffusion

modelVersions.name: v1.4-Tuned
modelVersions.description:
Right, 1.4.

This one took a couple weeks with around 12 to 20 hours of combination and weight tuning. Excel sheet to keep track of which one was better and everything.

The goal remains the same, just now with better eyes, background detail, and not completely deleting portions or tags that worked in previous versions.

Enjoy and see what you can crank out with this one!

For more information, see the v1.0 release notes!

items.name: Ass support / rest on object
items.description:
LoRA trained to generate a pose where the character is resting their buttocks on a bar shaped object like railing. This is a very simple LoRA I decided to make with some images I found associated with the concept of my other Ass support LoRA.

Please rate and leave a like if you enjoyed it! And be sure to follow to check out the upcoming models.

Trigger: ass support

You can try do use tags that identify an object similar to the image examples: railing, handrail, sword, sheath, katana, weapon, baseball bat, pipe, etc. If you want the character dressed, by describing their outfit, or you want to combine with character/clothes loras, you may need to increase this lora's weight quite a bit to see the effect. But don't worry, you can go up to e.g. 1.5 or 2.0 or more without affecting style or composition.

Additional info

I make these models for fun and for the challenge and release them for free for everyone to enjoy, for non-commercial use (see license). The one thing I ask of you is to provide rating and feedback! That helps me understand where I can improve and helps me stay motivated to produce more content! I accept suggestions or requests here or on Civitai discord server.

items.name: pyPromptChecker
items.description:
A tiny script for AI images created by AUTOMATIC/stable-diffusion-webui

For Linux and Windows. It operates stand alone. Now support PNG and JPEG

github https://github.com/yui-tan/pyPromptChecker

Notice : Please re-download the file if you downloaded it before 9/10 15:20 (UTC), as the initial upload may have been corrupted. I apologize for any inconvenience.

pyPromptChecker binary edition no longer has any requirements.

source code edition still require Python 3.x

If you do not wish to use the binary edition,
please run install.sh/install.bat file again after the upgrade to enable support for JPEG format files.

What's next

  • Diff mode

If you have any feedback, additional feature requests, or specific file formats you'd like me to support, please feel free to let me know. first come, first served.

Supports

  • Stable Diffusion Webui

    • Extras

    • Hires.fix

    • Dynamic Thresholding (CFG fix) extension

    • CFG auto

    • CFG scheduling

    • Add Network extension

    • ControlNet extension

    • Tiled diffusion extension

    • Regional prompter extension

  • Image format

    • PNG

    • JPEG

How to Install

Binary edition (both Linux and Windows users)

  1. Download the binary packages from here or github.

  2. Extract pyPromptChecker-bin directory to any location of your choice.

  3. Optionally, shortcut or desktop files for enable drag-and-drop functionality.

  4. Execute pyPromptChecker or pyPromptChecker.exe by double-click.

  5. If you are Linux user, you can delete pyPromptChecker.exe file.

  6. If you are Windows user, you can delete pyPromptChecker file.

Source code edition for Linux

git clone https://github.com/yui-tan/pyPromptChecker
cd pyPromptChecker/install
./install.sh

if you want to update.

cd /path/to/pyPromptChecker
git pull

Source code edition for Windows

  1. Make sure you've got Python 3.x hanging around.

  2. Download the packages.

  3. Extract the packages to a location of your choice as 'pyPromptChecker'.

  4. Run pyPromptChecker/install/install.bat file.

  5. Don't miss a single word of the words that pop up on the screen, before going wild in the comments.

How to Update

Using "git clone" during Installation

cd /path/to/pyPromptChecker
git pull

Using Packages during Installation:

  1. Download the latest package.

  2. Extract the new package to a location of your choice, but not the installed directory.

  3. Overwrite the following files and directories from the extracted package.

/pyPromptChecker/lib

/pyPromptChecker/__init__.py

/pyPromptChecker/main.py

  1. If necessary, also consider overwriting 'config.ini'.

  2. You might realize that it's pretty much the same thing as doing 'git pull'

How to Uninstall

Just delete entire directory.

items.name: Senna's McLaren MP4/4 Formula One (1988)
items.description:
V0.2 is the second training run with 27 images (x 5 repeats x 10 epochs) featuring only Ayrton Senna as driver (I'm sorry for Alain Prost but Ayrton is too iconic..) and with hand made captions and with cherry picked regularisation images, against SDXL 1.0 (VAE fix) base model.

Apparently with the Prodigy optimizer seems important to always keep the LoRA weight at 1, I want to do a new training session with more steps to better understand this behaviour..

In the previous version, identical in terms of parameters, but without regularisation images the wheels displacement was continuously a mess, now it seems that this has been improved.

As always all my models are works in progress, with plenty of room for improvement. Every suggestion and feedback is very welcome.. this is my main reason that drives me to be part of this community.

The McLaren MP4/4, also known as the McLaren-Honda MP4/4, is one of the most successful Formula One car designs of all time. Powered by Honda's RA168E 1.5-litre V6-turbo engine and driven by teammates Alain Prost and Ayrton Senna, the car competed during the 1988 Formula One season. The design of the car was led by American engineer Steve Nichols.

At the end of the season, McLaren-Honda had taken both the Constructors and Drivers' titles (Senna edging out Prost due to winning more races - only the eleven best results counted, so even though Prost scored more overall points, Senna's 8 first-place finishes to Prost's 7, meant Senna took the championship title.) McLaren-Honda, who scored a then-record 199 points in the Constructors Championship, wrapped up the Constructors title with a 1-2 finish in Belgium for Round 11 of the 16 race season, it was the team's eighth 1-2 finish of the season (Senna and Prost would finish 1-2 twice more, in Japan and Australia). The team finished the season a massive 134 points in front of 2nd placed Ferrari.

Elizabeth Lee McGovern (born July 18, 1961) is an American actress. She has received many awards, including a Screen Actors Guild Award, three Golden Globe Award nominations, and one Academy Award nomination.

Born in Evanston, Illinois, McGovern spent most of her early life in Los Angeles. After attending the American Conservatory Theater and the Juilliard School, she made her feature film debut in Ordinary People (1980). For her role as Evelyn Nesbit in the musical film Ragtime (1981), she received a nomination for the Academy Award for Best Supporting Actress. She subsequently had lead roles in a number of major studio films, including Once Upon a Time in America (1984), She's Having a Baby (1987), The Bedroom Window (1987), The Handmaid's Tale (1990), and The Wings of the Dove (1997).

items.name: Ether Moonlight Mix
items.description:
â˜… ğŸŒ™ Hello, this is Ether Moonlight Mix ğŸŒ™ â˜…

A fun little anime style model designed to replicate one of my favorite mediums - oil paintings!

Please keep in mind that this model has biases in generating females and humans.

âœ¨ Please Share Your Cool Creations Below! âœ¨

* Beta 1

An initial test release that, while not perfect, can still produce fun results.

Hey everyone. I mixed this model as a little side project. I wanted an anime, booru tag model that would output a style with thick brushwork reminescent of oil paintings.

I recommend utilizing words that describe mediums, such as oil painting, watercolor, gouache, which can further enhance the painterly effect. Additionally, evoking painters can do similar things. Try great painters and illustrators such as John Singer Sargent, Dean Cornwell and Anders Zorn.

Artist and style resources are a great way to both tune the style your outputs and learn more about art.

Still a lot to work on and improve, but I hope you have fun with what it can do!

* Huggingface Archive

ğŸš§ Information page is WIP, thanks for your patience. ğŸš§

â˜„ï¸ Generation Recommendations

Use whatever sampler, steps, CFG you prefer.

Most sample images were generated with:

  • Sampler: DPM++ 2M Karras

  • Steps: 20 - 28

  • CFG: 7 - 11

  • Clip Skip: 1

  • ENSD: 31337

Higher CFG can lead to more vibrant results.

Negative Prompt Example:

"NSFW, (worst quality, low quality:1.3), signature"

I recommend this simple negative prompt if you wish to achieve a similar style to the sample images.

Sample images were further upscaled using AUTO1111 Hi-res fix. Please utilize it if you wish to achieve similar results.

  • Latent (nearest-exact)

  • Upscale by: 2

  • Denoising strength: 0.55

Are your results changing too much after Hi-res fix? Please try 4x-foolhardy-Remarci.

  • 4x-foolhardy-Remarci

  • Upscale by: 2

  • Denoising strength: 0.45 - 0.55

Recommended VAE:

Waifu Diffusion VAE kl-f8-anime2

Strongly recommended as the model was tuned with this specific VAE's colors and saturation in mind.

ğŸ–Šï¸ Prompting Advice

As this is an anime style model I tuned it with booru style tag prompting, 1girl, long hair, jacket, etc. Of course you're free to prompt however you like. Mixing tags with prose can lead to fun results.

Utilizing words that describe mediums, such as oil painting, watercolor, gouache, can further enhance the painterly effect. Additionally, evoking painters can do similar things. Try great painters and illustrators such as John Singer Sargent, Dean Cornwell and Anders Zorn.

Artist and style resources are a great way to both tune the style your outputs and learn more about art.

If you look at the prompts included with the sample images they demonstrate that even with a very loose and vague style of prompting you can achieve fun, high quality images.

Try mixing natural language and booru-styled tags. Experiment and give the AI some freedom to interpret your ideas!

General guidelines:

  • Prompt in the style of anime/booru-style models, "masterpiece, best quality, ..... "

    • More anime style images, stronger bias towards females/humans

  • Prompt in the style of photography/non-anime models, "professional photograph of ..... "

    • More realistic images, higher style variety

ğŸ“˜ Model Merging Info - Beta 1

I have no training or real knowledge of machine learning. I merged the model using the information provided on WarriorMama777's AOM model page as well as the ones in these Rentrys. I very arbitrarily mixed the UBM weights of each model, modifying the values with trial and error until I was visually satisfied with it.

I utilized the SuperMerger extension for AUTO1111 by hako-mikan.
